Claims 1. A pixel sensor element (200) for generation of a signal from light falling on the pixel sensor element (200) comprising: a photodetector (201 ) arranged to generate a signal in response to light; a storage assembly comprising a number N of storage arrays (205), where N is 2 or more, each storage array (205) comprising: an input shift register (207) and an output shift register (215) each with a number M of storage cells arranged in a column, where M is 1 or more; and a storage shift register (21 1 ) with a number M of rows of storage cells, each row comprising a number P of storage cells, where P is 1 or more, arranged for signal transfer from the input shift register (207) to the output shift register (215); and a number N of independently driveable signal transfer regions (203), each arranged to be inducable to transfer the signal from the photodetector (201 ) to a first cell (210) of one of a respective one of the input shift registers (207); and a number N of signal read-out regions (219) each arranged to be inducable to read the signal from a last cell (217) of a respective one of the output shift registers (215), wherein the photodetector (201 ) is a single photodetector (201 ), and the N signal transfer regions (203) are arranged to be inducable to transfer the signal from the single photodetector (201 ). 2. A pixel sensor element (200) as claimed in claim 1 , wherein N is 4, the photodetector (201 ) is positioned in a central region of the pixel sensor element (200), and the 4 storage arrays (205) are positioned symmetrically around the photodetector (201 ). 3. A pixel sensor element (200) as claimed in claim 2, wherein the pixel sensor element (200) is square or rectangular in shape and wherein the 4 storage arrays (205) are positioned in different quadrants of the pixel sensor element (200). 4. A pixel sensor element (200) as claimed in any preceding claim, wherein the photodetector (201 ) is arranged to generate charge in response to light, wherein the input shift register (207), the output shift register (215), the storage shift register (21 1 ) are charge- coupled device, CCD, shift registers, and wherein the signal read-out regions (219) are arranged to convert charge read from the output shift registers (215) to generate a voltage or current signal. 5. An image sensor (300) comprising a plurality of pixel sensor elements (200) as claimed in any preceding claim, the pixel sensor elements (200) being arranged in an array of rows and columns with the photodetectors (201 ) arranged in rows (301 , 303, 305) and 

 comprising storage arrays (205) arranged in pairs of adjacent rows (307, 309) between the rows (301 , 303, 305) of photodetectors (201 ). 6. An image sensor (300) as claimed in claim 5 wherein for each pair of adjacent rows (307, 309) of storage arrays (205), each storage array (205) of a first of the pair of adjacent rows (307, 309) is operably connected to an adjacent storage array (205) of a second of the pair of adjacent rows (307, 309) to form a paired storage array (317), whereby each paired storage array (317) is arrangeable to act as a single storage array having an input shift register and an output shift register with 2M of storage cells arranged in a column and a storage shift register with 2M of rows of storage cells, each row having P storage cells. 7. An imaging device (400) comprising an image sensor (300) as claimed in claim 5 or claim 6, and a controller (401 ) operable to apply drive signals to the photodetectors (201 ) and storage cells of the pixel sensor elements (200) so as to control the frame rate of the photodetectors (201 ) and the signal transfer rate of the storage cells, wherein the controller (401 ) is operable to control the storage cells of the input shift registers (207) to transfer signals at 1/N the frame rate of the photodetector (201 ), and wherein the controller (401 ) is operable to control the storage cells of the storage shift registers (21 1 ) to transfer signals at 1/(N times M) the frame rate of the photodetector (201 ). 8. A storage assembly for storage and transfer of a signal from a single photodetector in a pixel sensor element, the storage assembly comprising: a number N of storage arrays (205), where N is 2 or more, each storage array (205) comprising: an input shift register (207) and an output shift register (215) each with a number M of storage cells arranged in a column, where M is 1 or more; and a storage shift register (21 1 ) with a number M of rows of storage cells, each row having a number P of storage cells, where P is 1 or more, arranged for signal transfer from the input shift register (207) to the output shift register (215), optionally wherein N is 4, and optionally wherein the input shift register (207), the output shift register (215), and the storage shift register (21 1 ) are charge-coupled device, CCD, shift registers. 9. A method of operating a pixel sensor element according to any of claims 1 to 4, the method comprising, for each storage array: (i) inducing the signal transfer region to transfer a signal from the photodetector to the first cell of the input shift register (S501 ); (ii) for at least one cell of the input shift register, transferring the signal from the cell of the input shift register to a first cell of a corresponding row of the storage shift register (S502); 

 (iii) for at least one row of the storage shift register, transferring the signal from a last cell of the row of the storage shift register to a corresponding cell of the output shift register (S503); (iv) inducing the signal read-out region to read the signal from the last cell of the output shift register (S504). 10. A method as claimed in claim 9, wherein (i) is repeated until the input shift register is full, and/or (ii) is performed in response to the input shift register being full. 1 1. A method as claimed in claim 9 or 10, wherein (ii) is performed until the storage shift register is full and/or (iii) is performed in response to the storage shift register being full. 12. A method as claimed in any of claims 9 to 1 1 , wherein the storage arrays are sequentially activated to perform (i) and/or (iv), and/or wherein the storage arrays are substantially simultaneously activated to perform (ii) and/or (iii). 13. A method as claimed in any of claims 9 to 12, wherein (i) is performed at 1/N the frame rate of the photodetector, (ii) and (iii) are performed at 1/(N times M) the frame rate of the photodetector. 14. A method of operating an image sensor according to claim 5, the method comprising: controlling each of the pixel sensor elements to perform the method of any of claims 9 to 13 (S601 ); using the signals provided by the signal read-out regions of each pixel sensor element to generate an image (S602). 15. A method of operating an image sensor according to claim 6, the method comprising, for each paired storage array: controlling a pixel sensor element including a first storage array of the paired storage array to perform the method of any of claims 9 to 13 (S701 ); controlling a pixel sensor element including a second storage array of the paired storage array to, for the second storage array: (i) receive at the input shift register, a signal from a last cell of the input shift register of the first storage array (S702); (ii) for at least one cell of the input shift register, transfer the signal from the cell of the input shift register to a first cell of a corresponding row of the storage shift register (S703); 

 (iii) for at least one row of the storage shift register, transfer the signal from a last cell of the row of the storage shift register to a corresponding cell of the output shift register (S704); and (iv) transfer the signal from the output shift register to a first cell of the output shift register of the first storage array (S705).
